    "definitions": [
      {
        "definition": "Soil organic matter comprises all living and dead biological material in the soil, including decomposed plant material, animal remains, microbial biomass, and humic compounds. It is determined by loss-on-ignition or wet oxidation and reported as a percentage of oven-dried soil weight. Organic matter content controls nutrient cycling, water-holding capacity, and soil structure.",
        "sources": null,
        "tags": [
          "Soil Composition Analysis"
        ]
